I came to meet him on a Saturday and spent about an hour outside his kennel before leaving without him. After sleeping on it, I rushed back Sunday morning and adopted him. Since then, a lot has happened. My father unexpectedly passed away in February 2017, I had to move in April 2017 and Larry had to get used to a small apartment! Heâ€™s been the best therapy this year. I take him everywhere Iâ€™m allowed- dog parks, restaurants, the beach, work! He is still pretty shy at first, but warms up to everyone pretty quickly.
